Jakadan Amurka ya zargi kasar Sin da yin "bullying" da "tallan-tallan"
Wata mako bayan wata jaridar kasar Sin ta wallafa wata sanarwa mai shafuka hudu a wata jaridar Amurka inda ake tallata amfanin cinikin Amurka da China, jakadan Amurka a kasar Sin ya zargi Beijing da amfani da jaridar Amurka wajen yada labaran ta.
A ranar Laraba da ta gabata ne shugaban Amurka Donald Trump ya yi magana game da karin kudin da China Daily ke bayarwa a cikin jaridar Des Moines Register, jaridar da ta fi sayarwa a Iowa, bayan ya zargi kasar Sin da son tsoma baki a zaben majalisar dokokin Amurka na 6 ga watan Nuwamba, wani abu da kasar Sin ta musanta.
Zargin da Trump ya yi game da ƙoƙarin Beijing na yin tasiri a zaben Amurka ya nuna abin da jami'an Amurka suka nuna wa Reuters a matsayin sabon mataki a cikin wani gagarumin yakin neman zaben da Washington ta fara na matsa lamba kan China.
Duk da yake gwamnatocin kasashen waje suna yin tallace-tallace don inganta kasuwancin su, Beijing da Washington a halin yanzu suna cikin rikici na cinikayya wanda ya sa suka ƙara yawan harajin da ake amfani da shi a kan kayayyakin da suke shigowa daga bangarorin biyu.
An yi tunanin cewa harajin da kasar Sin ta yi amfani da shi a farkon yakin kasuwanci zai shafi masu fitar da kayayyaki daga jihohi kamar Iowa, wadanda suka goyi bayan Jam'iyyar Republican ta Trump, a cewar masana na kasar Sin da Amurka.
Terry Branstad, jakadan Amurka a kasar Sin kuma tsohon gwamnan Iowa, wanda shi ne babban mai fitar da kayayyakin gona zuwa kasar Sin, ya ce Beijing ta yi wa ma'aikatan Amurka, manoma da 'yan kasuwa lahani.
Branstad ya rubuta a cikin wata sanarwa a cikin jaridar Des Moines Register a ranar Lahadi cewa, kasar Sin "ta ƙara matsa lamba da buga tallace-tallace a cikin jaridarmu ta kyauta".
Branstad ya rubuta cewa: "Don yaɗa wannan propaganda, gwamnatin Sin ta yi amfani da al'adar Amirka ta 'yancin yin magana da kuma 'yancin buga labarai ta wajen wallafa wani sanarwa a cikin Des Moines Register", in ji Branstad.
"A maimakon haka, a tashar tashar da muke a nan Beijing, an ga wasu muryoyi da ba su dace ba kuma babu wani ainihin tunani game da ra'ayoyin da mutane a China za su iya yi game da yadda tattalin arzikin kasarsu ke tafiya, tun da yake an yi wa kafofin watsa labarai iko da matsin lamba na Jam'iyyar Kwaminis ta Sin", in ji ta.
Ya kara da cewa "daya daga cikin jaridu mafi girma a kasar Sin ya yi watsi da tayin buga" labarinsa, ko da yake bai bayyana wane jarida ne.
